%N A393948 Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} ((1-1/p)^2 * Product_{k>=0} (1 + 2/p^(2^k))).
%C A393948 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random equals 1 (i.e., they are infinitarily coprime).
%F A393948 Equals 2*A327576. - _Artur Jasinski_, Mar 04 2026
%e A393948 0.733250553890763819113065441374003126067224311942018...
%o A393948 (PARI) c(m) = prodeulerrat((1 - 1/p)^2 * prod(k = 0, m, 1 + 2/p^(2^k)));
%o A393948 {my(c1 = 0, c2 = 1, m = 1); while(c2 != c1, c1 = c2; c2 = c(m); m++); c2}
%Y A393948 Cf. A064380, A077609, A327576.
%Y A393948 Analogous constants: A059956, A306071.
%Y A393948 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is: A065472 (square), this constant (1), A393949 (prime), A393950 (squarefree), A393951 (Fermi-Dirac prime), A393952 (exponentially 2^n-number), A393953 (4th power).
%K A393948 nonn,cons
